library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

set.seed(123)

# Number of hypothetical samples
n_hypo <- 20

# Store sample size explicitly
sample_size <- nrow(Scores)

# Create resampled datasets
hop_data <- lapply(1:n_hypo, function(i) {
  Scores %>%
    slice_sample(n = sample_size, replace = TRUE) %>%
    mutate(sample_id = i)
}) %>% bind_rows()

# Plot HOP
ggplot(hop_data, aes(x = Group, y = OverallScores)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5, position = position_jitter(width = 0.15)) +
  facet_wrap(~ sample_id) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Hypothetical Outcome Plot (HOP): Wonderlic Scores by Position",
    subtitle = "Each panel is one hypothetical sample drawn from the observed data",
    x = "Position",
    y = "Wonderlic Score"
  )
